The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Loose Change
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     LOOSE CHANGE
                              
	 ICICI Bank has launched a global Indian account facility, under which customers will get a kit comprising the host country bank account, debit card and Internet banking deliverables prior to their departure from India. The facility will be available for Indians moving to the UK, the US and Canada for work, study or immigration. Along with this account, customers will also get a non-resident rupee account, which will help in instant money transfers between the host country account and the India account.                            
	 ICICI Bank is issuing tax-saving bonds at 6 per cent. There are four options maturing in 36-64 months. Each offers tax exemption under Section 88. The annual yield, including tax savings, ranges between 9.1 per cent and 12 per cent. The face value is Rs 5,000 and the maximum application is for 20 bonds. The issue closes on September 9.                             
	 ICICI Lombard General Insurance has launched a claims service initiative called Red Carpet for its motor insurance business. An individual insuring 50 vehicles is classified as a Red Carpet customer and is offered hassle-free documentation and quick claims settlement. It also involves relaxation in spot survey if the surveyor does not turn up within six hours and the claim is paid without any deduction.                                                                                                                             
